   <body>
      <p>Activating a program triggers jobs to create payout schedules. Primarily these payout schedules are created based on the settings of three attributes on the Program Definition.</p>
      <p>The attributes include:</p>
      <p>
         <table>
            <tgroup cols="2">
               <colspec colname="col1"/>
               <colspec colname="col2"/>
               <thead>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Fields</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Billing Frequency</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>The setting defines, the schedule frequency Monthly, Quarterly, Semi-Annual, and Yearly.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Program Schedule Day</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>The setting defines the dates to be considered for a period generation.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Ready For Invoice Day</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>The setting defines, the maximum number of days to accept the order lines for a previous period, before changing the status of the period to calculation complete.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
